  "description": [
    "WEST NEWS AND QUOTATIONS OF THE FINANCIAL MARKETS LINCOLN BANK TO OPEN NEW BRANCH Monday Selected for Formal Opening in Charge of Wal lace McK Stowell By HARRY GUSACK Furnished throughout with the most modern banking equipment the branch office of the Lincoln National Bank at Seventeenth and H Streets northwest will open its doors for business Monday morning it was announced by officials of that institution today Stowell As Manager The branch office will be in charge of Wallace McK Stowell assistant cashier who has been with the parent institution since its inception Mr Stowell is well known in local banking circles is past president of the Washington chapter of the American Institute of Banking and officials of the bank predict a splendid growth for the branch office under his man agement Frank J Rice manager of the savings department of the main bank will also be connected with the branch office it was stated Mr Rice has been With the Lincoln National Bank for the past six teen years The branch office will remain open until 9 p m Monday in order that the banks many friends and depositors may have an opportunity to inspect the new quarters"
  ],
